nsive interview material, Steve Chibnall traces Lee Thompson's career in British cinema, and offers an analysis of his films which reveals remarkable, and previously unacknowledged, continuities of style and theme.This is a book for anyone interested in the history of British cinema, and particularly those who enjoy the best of 1950s and 1960s film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszGreat BritainvBiography. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAmerican film.  aBritish cinema.  aCarol Reed.  aHollywood.  aLee Thompson.  aMidshipman Easy.  aMurder Without Crime.  aSecond World War.  aThe Yellow Balloon.  aYoung Woodley.  asocial critique.  aversatile director.1 aChibnall, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614148440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141484423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141484/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles